Date: Fri, 19 Dec 2008 03:37:52 -0800
From: Yinghai Lu <>
Subject: [PATCH] x86: fix used_vectors breakage
Sender: linux-kernel-owner@vger.kernel.org
Precedence: bulk
List-ID: <linux-kernel.vger.kernel.org>
X-Mailing-List: linux-kernel@vger.kernel.org
X-Lkml-Link: https://lkml.org/lkml/2008/12/19/68

Impact: fix and clean up
32bit used used_vectors to record vectors..., after we change it to
per_cpu vector it is broken.
try enable that for 64bit, and the array is used to for all vectors that
is not managed by vector_irq per_cpu array.
also kill system_vectors[], that is duplicated with used_vectors bitmap
Signed-off-by: Yinghai Lu <yinghai@kernel.org>
